indicators.justification:
EGR.GOV.BY's SSL and API don't work (1). From January 18, 2021, five modernized electronic services of the Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Belarus (Ministry of Justice) are available on the unified portal of electronic services (EPES)(2).

The updated web services are built taking into account the requirements of the REST architectural style, as well as the transition to the technology of interaction with the national automated information system (OAIS) through the OAIS API control core. Thus, the web services of the following electronic services of the UAIS have changed based on information from the state information resource "The Unified State Register of Legal Entities and Individual Entrepreneurs" of the Ministry of Justice (USR):

"Information on legal entities and individual entrepreneurs by name";
"Information about legal entities and individual entrepreneurs by registration number";
"Brief information about legal entities and individual entrepreneurs by registration number";
 "Information about the separate subdivisions of a legal entity (branches, representative offices) as of a certain date";
"Information about a legal entity, an individual entrepreneur for a period of time by registration number."
Also, on January 18, 2021, 5 new electronic services of the Ministry of Justice were put into operation at the EPEU based on information from the USR:
"List of business entities in which an individual is listed as a manager/liquidator (without history)";
"Obtaining an extract from the Unified State Register of Legal Entities and Individual Entrepreneurs in the form of a file
in RTF format ";
"Obtaining information about a state body (state legal entity, the position of which is approved by an act of legislation)";
"Obtaining a list of legal entities in which an individual is listed as the owner of the property (founder, participant)
with history ";
"Obtaining a list of legal entities in which the legal entity is listed as the owner of the property (founder, participant)
with history ".

The recipients of services are state organizations subordinate (accountable) to the President of the Republic of Belarus or subordinate to the Council of Ministers of the Republic of Belarus, the National Academy of Sciences of Belarus, organizations for state registration of real estate, rights to it and transactions with it, notaries, republican government bodies, other state bodies and government bodies, their structural subdivisions with the rights of a legal entity and territorial bodies, courts, prosecution bodies, local executive and administrative bodies (their structural subdivisions with the rights of a legal entity), bailiffs.

Services are rendered using the system-system technology with strong authentication (using a valid private key of an electronic digital signature).

From January 18, 2021, a new electronic service "Providing Information from the Databank of Enforcement Proceedings" is available based on information from the Databank of Enforcement Proceedings of the Ministry of Justice.

The service can be received by citizens of the Republic of Belarus, foreign citizens and stateless persons, individual entrepreneurs of the Republic of Belarus, foreign individual entrepreneurs, legal entities of the Republic of Belarus, foreign legal entities and organizations that are not legal entities, notaries, courts, and other state bodies.

This electronic service is provided both through a single portal of electronic services (free of charge) and using the system-system technology (on a reimbursable basis according to the price list of tariffs for electronic services of the OAIS and free of charge in accordance with the legislative acts of the Republic of Belarus)(3).

